sequenceDiagram
    actor "Client Contact" as ClientContact
    participant "Frontend SPA" as FrontendSPA
    participant "Backend API" as BackendAPI
    participant "Primary Database" as PrimaryDatabase
    participant "Audit Log Database" as AuditLogDatabase
    participant "Email Service" as EmailService

    activate FrontendSPA
    ClientContact->>FrontendSPA: 1. 1. Clicks secure link from approval email.
    FrontendSPA-->>ClientContact: Page load request is initiated.
    activate BackendAPI
    FrontendSPA->>BackendAPI: 2. 2. GET /api/v1/milestone-approvals/{token}
    BackendAPI-->>FrontendSPA: 200 OK with Milestone data or Error Response.
    BackendAPI->>BackendAPI: 2.1. 2a. Validate token (signature, expiry, format).
    BackendAPI-->>BackendAPI: Token validity status.
    activate PrimaryDatabase
    BackendAPI->>PrimaryDatabase: 2.2. 2b. Fetch Milestone & Token data.
    PrimaryDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Milestone, Project, Client records; Token status.
    FrontendSPA->>ClientContact: 3. 3. Renders milestone details with 'Approve' and 'Reject' options.
    ClientContact-->>FrontendSPA: User views the page.
    ClientContact->>FrontendSPA: 4. 4. Clicks 'Approve'.
    FrontendSPA-->>ClientContact: Initiates POST request.
    FrontendSPA->>BackendAPI: 5. 5. POST /api/v1/milestone-approvals/{token}/approve
    BackendAPI-->>FrontendSPA: 200 OK (Success) or Error Response.
    BackendAPI->>PrimaryDatabase: 6. 6. **BEGIN ATOMIC TRANSACTION**
    PrimaryDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Transaction started.
    BackendAPI->>PrimaryDatabase: 6.1. 6a. Verify token is not used and update Milestone status.
    PrimaryDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Update result.
    BackendAPI->>PrimaryDatabase: 6.2. 6b. Invalidate token.
    PrimaryDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Update result.
    activate AuditLogDatabase
    BackendAPI->>AuditLogDatabase: 6.3. 6c. Log approval event.
    AuditLogDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Log entry created.
    BackendAPI->>PrimaryDatabase: 6.4. 6d. **COMMIT TRANSACTION**
    PrimaryDatabase-->>BackendAPI: Transaction committed.
    activate EmailService
    BackendAPI->>EmailService: 7. 7. Send notification to System Admin.
    FrontendSPA->>ClientContact: 8. 8. Display 'Milestone Approved' confirmation message.

    note over BackendAPI: SECURITY: Token is a short-lived JWT containing milestoneId and clientId as claims. Its hash is s...
    note over BackendAPI: ATOMICITY: Steps 6a, 6b, and 6c are executed within a single database transaction to ensure data ...

    deactivate EmailService
    deactivate AuditLogDatabase
    deactivate PrimaryDatabase
    deactivate BackendAPI
    deactivate FrontendSPA
